DIAMOND STATE GENERATION PARTNERS, LLC MARKET-BASED RATE TARIFF 1. Availability: Diamond State Generation Partners, LLC ("DSGP") makes electric energy, capacity and ancillary services available under this Market-Based Rate Tariff ("Tariff") to any purchaser, except as prohibited below, with whom DSGP has contracted. 2. Applicability: This Tariff is applicable to all wholesale sales of electric energy, capacity and ancillary services by DSGP at market-based rates. 3. Rates: All sales shall be made at rates established by agreement between the purchaser and DSGP. 4. Other Terms and Conditions: All other terms and conditions shall be established by agreement between the purchaser and DSGP. 5. Seller Category: DSGP is a Category 1 Seller in all regions, as defined in 18 C.F.R. ? 35.36(a). 6. Compliance with Commission Regulations: DSGP shall comply with the provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission ("Commission") imposes in its orders concerning DSGP's market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes DSGP to engage in affiliate sales under this Tariff or otherwise restricts or limits DSGP's market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning DSGP's market-based rate authority will constitute a violation of this Tariff. 7. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority: 7.1 DSGP has received waiver of: Subparts B and C of Part 35, except for sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15 and 35.16; Part 41, Part 101 (with the exception that waiver of the provisions of Part 101 that apply to hydropower licensees has not been granted with respect to licensed hydropower projects), and Part 141, except for sections 141.14 and 141.15; and has received blanket approval under Part 34. Diamond State Generation Partners, LLC, Letter Order, Docket Nos. ER12-1383-000 and ER12-1383-001 (2012). 7.2 DSGP's authorization to sell capacity and/or energy at market-based rates pursuant to this Tariff is restricted in mitigated balancing authorities, and is further restricted as described in Alabama Power Company, 163 FERC ? 61,090, PP31-33 (2018); Alabama Power Company, 158 FERC ? 61,131, P 21 (2017); Southern Company Services, Inc., 129 FERC ? 61,222, P 8 (2009), Southern Company Services, Inc., 125 FERC ? 61,317 (2008).
8. Ancillary Services: DSGP offers regulation and frequency response service, energy imbalance service, and operating reserve service (which includes spinning, 10-minute, and 30-minute reserves) for sale into the market administered by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") and, where the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff permits, the self-supply of these services to purchasers for a bilateral sale that is used to satisfy the ancillary services requirements of the PJM Office of Interconnection. 9. Revisions to Tariff: DSGP may file revisions to this Tariff with the Commission. Nothing contained in this Tariff shall be construed as affecting or limiting in any way the right of DSGP to unilaterally file with the Commission for a change in any aspect of this Tariff under Section 205 of the Federal Power Act pursuant to the Commission's Rules and Regulations promulgated thereunder. 10. Effective Date: This Rate Schedule is effective on such date as set by the Commission. 1
